{"author":{"id":"75732e82453cc4795a3b5d7bef7a9ce916b428e5bbe06161843f7392657be5c1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1445425622,"nonce":"gQ4/8RfwvHS70N2fsWX/uK1RxsE=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE0OTg1NjkyNA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/345#issuecomment-149856924"},"message":"\u003e That said, I agree with your points. If anyone else feels similarly I'll add a script which will have to always be running, to map URLs to files on disk.\n\nIt shouldn't be always running. Just the tabular file you have would be sufficient. Rather than using the sha256sum as uid you could use the url as a uid.\n\nWhat I like about @bgruening's idea is that it requires PRs and some kind of checking before URLs get in the system.\n\n\u003e  We do not need to store the checksum inside of the tool_dependency as this script will take care of it.\n\nAs long as the proxy server doesn't get hacked. The current implementation works like a 2-factor authentication because the checksums are not provided by the servers that host the packages (github excluded, but you get the point)","files":null}]}